{
  "stem": "868.4",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And their job was water tanks and repairs of damaged military vehicles.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "So they went all through Florence distributing water to the civilian population, and they took over a garage where all the jeeps and another military vehicles from the front came back damaged and had to be fixed.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I was adopted by them.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I slept with them.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "I worked with them.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "I ate with-- with-- with-- with them.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "When the orphanage was liberated, we went back, of course, to visit and all that.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And the kids where amazed to hear that we were not what we said we were, with names totally different.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Not French, not Italian, not even Catholics.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "To [INAUDIBLE], we were Jews.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "They couldn't get this.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "It didn't sink in.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This was so-- they weren't convinced.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "One of them said, so you speak other languages, too, right?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I said, yes.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I said, even Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Say something in Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Say something in-- in Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So I said, well, I'm glad I have lived this day to be able to talk to you like-- like that, which they didn't understand.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But the strange-sounding words convinced them we were other than what they thought they were.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I remained with that military unit until it became known that [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] the British Mandate authorities would now allow Jews to go to Israel.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I have to backtrack a little bit.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "At the beginning of the war, Jewish immigration to Israel was restricted by the White Paper, which was a government policy to restrict Jewish immigration so as not to offend the Arab population.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And immigration to Israel was strictly limited, but they had issued a number of certificates for those people wanting to immigrate to Israel.",
      "word_count": 23
    }
  ],
